{
  "local_port": 52906,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "I have a problem with coupon set up. I have created a coupon in WooCommerce and I want it to be applied to the product on sale. I have also removed the check from the exclude sale item. But still it's not applying that coupon to products which are on sale. How can I fix it?",
  "response": "There could be multiple reasons why the coupon is not being applied to sale items in WooCommerce. Here are some steps you can follow to troubleshoot and fix the issue:\n\n1. **Coupon Settings:**\n   - **Discount Type:** Ensure that the discount type is set correctly. Some types may not apply to sale items.\n   - **Usage Restrictions:** Double-check all the usage restrictions set for the coupon. Make sure there are no conditions preventing it from applying to sale items.\n   - **Usage Limits:** Verify the usage limit per coupon and usage limit per user. If these limits are reached, the coupon won't be applied.\n\n2. **Compatibility with Other Plugins:**\n   - **Plugin Conflicts:** Sometimes other plugins can interfere with coupon functionality. Temporarily disable other plugins to see if the coupon works on sale items.\n   - **Cache Plugins:** Clear your site cache if you're using any caching plugins. Cached data might be causing the issue.\n\n3. **Theme Overrides:**\n   - If your theme has custom WooCommerce templates, up-to-date theme files might overwrite the default WooCommerce templates, causing the coupon settings issue.\n\n4. **WooCommerce Settings:**\n   - **Coupon Management:** Go to WooCommerce > Settings > General and ensure that \"Enable the use of coupon codes\" is checked.\n   - **Sale Price Handling:** Check how WooCommerce handles discounts on sale items. There might be an option to enable/disable the combination of sale prices and coupons.\n\n5. **Testing:**\n   - Create a new basic coupon with minimal settings, like a fixed cart discount, and test it on a sale item.\n   - If it works, gradually re-add your restrictions to see which one causes the job failure.\n\n6. **Update & Maintenance:**\n   - Ensure both WooCommerce and your theme are up-to-date. Incompatibilities might arise from outdated versions.\n    \n7. **Debug Mode:**\n   - Enable WooCommerce debugging mode to check for errors. You can find these settings under WooCommerce > Status > Logs.\n\n8. **WooCommerce Support:**\n   - If the issue persists, it might be worth reaching out to WooCommerce support or checking their documentation for any known issues or updates on this feature.\n\nBy methodically going through these steps, you should be able to identify the barrier preventing coupon use on sale items and resolve the issue accordingly.",
